Introduction

Code Kunst is a is a South Korean rapper, composer and music producer. He joined the record label HIGHGRND under YG Entertainment in September 2015 due to the impact of Tablo of Epik High. In June of 2018 he moved into Jay Park's record label AOMG.

Fun facts

1
The word "Kunst" means "Art" in German, therefore the stage name "Code Kunst" has a meaning of "the music I produced will become arts."
…
2
Code Kunst was in the same team with The Quiett. Together they produced "Go High" (feat. Changmo, Woo Won-jae), sung by female rapper Lee Young-ji, who became the final winner of the show.
…
3
In the same year of 2019, Code Kunst appeared in another Hip-hop reality survival program "High School Rapper 3".
…
4
In 2019, Code Kunst, along with Jay Park, Simon Dominic, Woo Won-jae, and Gray, appeared as judges on the audition program Signhere started by Korean Hip-hop label AOMG and MBN.
…
5
In 2018, Code Kunst collaborated with various Korean hip-hop artists including Nafla, Loopy, Kid Milli etc.
…
6
Code Kunst started his music career relevantly later in his life, after serving in the military.
…
7
Loopy and Kid Milli from his team won second and third place in "Show Me the Money 777".
…
8
He then was nominated by Korean Hip-Hop Awards for Best Producer in 2019.
…
9
In September 2018, Code Kunst officially appeared in the Korean Hip-Hop survival show "Show Me the Money 777" as one of the judges.
…
10
He is also a member of Legit Goons crew, which consists of composers, rappers, engineers, and filmmakers.
…
